						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biotechnology/Related-developments/Nigeria-improved-cowpea-varieties-hit-Nigeria-s-savannah" title="Nigeria: improved cowpea varieties hit Nigeria's savannah" alt="link">Nigeria: improved cowpea varieties hit Nigeria's savannah</a></h2>

	
					<p>Nigeria has released two new cowpea varieties to raise production and improve farmers' incomes. The varieties were developed in Nigerian research institutions. The varieties - so far going under the technical names IT89KD-288 and IT89KD-391 - were developed by scientists working at four Nigerian universities and research centers. &quot;Both varieties have proven superiority over the current improved lines being cultivated and aim to overcome the challenges faced by cowpea farmers in the country,&quot; according to researchers. (Source: afrol News, 16 April 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
